1 Terraforming Mars

My #1 of all time is no suprise for those who knows me. Ever since I first played Terraforming Mars at a convention about 18 months before it was released (@FryxGames are always at that convention) it has been one of my favourite games.

Merry Christmas! https://t.co/kHs08OGYgU

2 A Feast for Odin

My #2 of all time is A Feast for Odin. As you can see in my top list, Uwe Rosenberg is one of my favourite designers. And this is his master piece. Worker Placement is also my favourite mechanism! https://t.co/yk20PyjPuw

3 Tapestry

My #3 of all time is Tapestry. I've always been very fond of civ type games, and this is one of the quicker ones. The production is fantastic. With the first expansion there are also so many different civs to try so there is high replayability. https://t.co/UHVLoEWUsk

4 Fields of Arle

My #4 of all time is the amazing 2-player game Fields of Arle. It's a farming game like many other Uwe Rosenberg games. And with the expansion you can play up to 3 players. Good solo game too. https://t.co/0X7HbJxiYV

5 Great Western Trail

My #5 of all time is Great Western Trail. I've only played the first edition (with expansion). Going to try the 2nd edition at BGA. https://t.co/HiUGTZ0e1J

6 Hallertau

My #6 of all time is my favourite game from 2020, Hallertau. A nice twist on worker placement and enough cards to ensure replayability. https://t.co/ZWUGnFWcLu

7 Indonesia

My #7 of all time is Indonesia. An amazing economic game by Splotter. We've had many fantastic games of Indonesia during the years, but it doesn't hit the table as often now. https://t.co/fQ5trORZOt

8 Lost Ruins of Arnak

My #8 of all time is Lost Ruins of Arnak. A tricky game with a small deck building element. And the production of this game is amazing! I just got the expansion this week, can't wait to try it! https://t.co/QH83GyK2Po

9 Caverna: The Cave Farmers

My #9 of all time is Caverna. This completely replaced Agricola for me. And with another expansion coming in 2022, this will probably get played a lot when that shows up. https://t.co/7Zs3jHgcDi

12 Le Havre

My #12 of all times is Le Havre. This Uwe Rosenberg classic never gets old. Too bad I don't have the expansion, which seems impossible to get (and I think is now included in newer versions). I like it at all player counts, even if it's best at 3 or 4. https://t.co/EYv7motTyG
